This paper is about training binary weight networks for computer vision tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks (cs.LG) and optimization methods (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of low-bit weight representation for efficient network inference, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve image datasets, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
